<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="369" pageId="5" pageNumber="368" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,417,586]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,372,489,514]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">Redescription.</emphasis>
Length of forewing 14.0–18.0mm; forewing expanse 26.0–36.7mm. Head, thorax and abdomen resembling those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari, 2016" authorityName="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari" authorityYear="2016" box="[502,593,525,549]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="368" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[502,593,525,549]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">S. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[604,697,525,550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[604,697,525,550]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but different as follows: Vertex and face roughly clothed with yellowish white long hairs.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1053651/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="368" targetBox="[169,1404,624,1911]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1940,2023]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,272,1940,1962]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">FIGURE 5</emphasis>
. Male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zagulajev" authorityYear="1965" box="[479,611,1940,1962]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="368" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amurensis">
<emphasis box="[479,611,1940,1962]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">
S. 
<taxonomicName box="[508,611,1941,1962]" pageId="5" pageNumber="368" rank="species" species="amurensis">amurensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A: whole genitalia except aedeagus, lateral view. B: Uncus, dorsal view. C: Genitalia except valva, ventral view. D: Valva, inner view. E: Anellus and juxta, lateral view. F: Aedeagus, lateral view. G: 
<emphasis box="[151,203,2002,2023]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="368">Ditto</emphasis>
, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1053653/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" targetBox="[170,1426,211,1370]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1413,1466]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,270,1413,1435]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">FIGURE 6</emphasis>
. Female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zagulajev" authorityYear="1965" box="[489,618,1414,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amurensis">
<emphasis box="[489,618,1414,1435]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">S. amurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A: whole genitalia, lateral view. B: Terminalia, ventral view. C: Genital plate, ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1510,2003]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
Wing markings (
<figureCitation box="[395,487,1510,1535]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1287,1309]" captionTargetBox="[411,1179,205,1247]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[396,1192,195,1263]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adults of Scardia species from Japan. A: S. fusca sp. nov., holotype ♂. B: S. amurensis ♂." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1053643/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
): Forewing and hindwing resembling those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari, 2016" authorityName="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari" authorityYear="2016" box="[1043,1134,1511,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1043,1134,1511,1535]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">S. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1146,1239,1510,1535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1146,1239,1510,1535]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but different as follows: Forewing upperside bordered with yellowish white along dorsum and termen. Hindwing upperside pale brownish white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1510,2003]" box="[199,1054,1618,1643]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
Wing venation (
<figureCitation box="[379,468,1618,1643]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1400,1422]" captionTargetBox="[444,1143,205,1368]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[426,1154,193,1385]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. wing venations of Scardia species. A: S. fusca sp. nov., ♂. B: S. amurensis ♂." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1053645/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
): Wing venation resembling that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari, 2016" authorityName="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari" authorityYear="2016" box="[870,957,1619,1643]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[870,957,1619,1643]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">S. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[964,1054,1618,1643]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[964,1054,1618,1643]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1510,2003]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[375,444,1654,1679]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1940,1962]" captionTargetBox="[169,1404,624,1911]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[159,1419,610,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male genitalia of S. amurensis. A: whole genitalia except aedeagus, lateral view. B: Uncus, dorsal view. C: Genitalia except valva, ventral view. D: Valva, inner view. E: Anellus and juxta, lateral view. F: Aedeagus, lateral view. G: Ditto, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1053651/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
): Male genitalia resembling those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari, 2016" authorityName="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari" authorityYear="2016" box="[863,950,1655,1679]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[863,950,1655,1679]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">S. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[957,1047,1654,1679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[957,1047,1654,1679]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but different as follows: Width of base of uncus similar to length of uncus. Gnathos and subscaphium absent. Vinculum broad; saccus broad with rounded apex. Valva 1/2 as wide as height of ring, valval apodeme 1/4 times as long as length of valva. Carina of phallus projecting.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1510,2003]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[407,481,1798,1823]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1413,1435]" captionTargetBox="[170,1426,211,1370]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,193,1392]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female genitalia of S. amurensis. A: whole genitalia, lateral view. B: Terminalia, ventral view. C: Genital plate, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1053653/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
): Female genitalia resembling those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari, 2016" authorityName="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari" authorityYear="2016" box="[945,1036,1799,1823]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[945,1036,1799,1823]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">S. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1046,1140,1798,1823]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1046,1140,1798,1823]" pageId="6" pageNumber="369">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but different as follows. Genital plate with a pair of rounded quadrate lamellae; apical 1/4 of digitiform process extending beyond posterior margin of genital plate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
