<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="370" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1396,1889]" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1757,1782]" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zagulajev" authorityYear="1965" box="[565,772,1757,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amurensis">
<emphasis box="[565,772,1757,1781]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">Scardia amurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari, 2016" authorityName="Osada &amp; Sakai &amp; Hirowatari" authorityYear="2016" box="[825,912,1757,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[825,912,1757,1781]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">S. fusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[919,1008,1757,1782]" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[919,1008,1757,1782]" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[1263,1389,1757,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boletella">
<emphasis box="[1263,1389,1757,1781]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">S. boletella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[151,281,1793,1816]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasia">
<emphasis box="[151,281,1793,1816]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">S. caucasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in lateral view, but the uncal lobes are slenderer, and not stout as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[1081,1209,1793,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boletella">
<emphasis box="[1081,1209,1793,1817]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">S. boletella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1267,1397,1793,1816]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caucasia">
<emphasis box="[1267,1397,1793,1816]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">S. caucasia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, in the two Japanese species, the digitiform processes of the female are slenderer than those of other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1830" box="[151,237,1865,1889]" class="Insecta" family="Tineidae" genus="Scardia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="370" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,237,1865,1889]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="370">Scardia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
